The paper introduces a new notion of tree-width for first order formulae and discusses its applications in model checking and comparison with other related notions such as elimination-width and strict tree-width. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the logic (cs.LO) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves algorithmic and complexity analysis, which could make it relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses applications in artificial intelligence, specifically in the context of cops and robbers games, which could make it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
